title: Rosie Perez testifies Annabella Sciorra told her about alleged rape by Harvey Weinstein
description: Actress Rosie Perez took the stand in Harvey Weinstein's trial Friday to support her friend Annabella Sciorra, who testified Thursday the disgraced movie mogul raped her in the winter of 1993-94.

title: 1 person is in custody after Naval Station Great Lakes was put on lockdown
description: Naval Station Great Lakes in Illinois is on lockdown, according to the base's Facebook page.

title: Teen accused of killing his mother and twin 13-year-old brothers before going to school
description: An Alabama teenager has been arrested for allegedly killing his mother and twin 13-year-old brothers.

title: Snakes could be the source of the Wuhan coronavirus outbreak
description: Snakes -- the Chinese krait and the Chinese cobra -- may be the original source of the newly discovered coronavirus that has triggered an outbreak of a deadly infectious respiratory illness in China this winter.

title: Dems invoke McCain during Senate impeachment trial
description: Impeachment House manager Rep. Adam Schiff (D-CA) used video footage of late Sen. John McCain during the Senate impeachment trial to exemplify the threat posed by Russia on Ukraine over the course of history, and to reinforce the notion that support for Ukraine is critical to US national security.

title: Davos ends with disagreement on climate and Greta Thunberg on the march
description: The annual meeting of the world's business and political leaders in Davos wrapped up Friday with two of the world's most powerful people disagreeing over how to address the climate crisis and youth activists excoriating the global elite for not doing enough to prevent global warming.

title: Puppy gets head stuck in wheel, firefighters step in
description: Firefighters in California rescued a 3-month-old puppy after its head got stuck in a wheel.

title: 34 US service members suffered traumatic brain injuries after Iran missile strike
description: Thirty-four US service members have been diagnosed with traumatic brain injuries following the Iranian missile attack on US forces in Iraq earlier this month, Pentagon spokesman Jonathan Hoffman said Friday.

title: Hong Kong's most famous fortune teller makes 2020 predictions
description: It's the busiest time of the year for So Man-fung Peter, one of the most famous geomancy consultants in Hong Kong.

title: Social media videos appear to show overcrowded hospitals
description: Social media videos appear to show patients overcrowd hospitals in Wuhan -- a city under partial lockdown -- due to the Wuhan coronavirus outbreak. CNN's David Culver reports.

title: Taylor Swift shares she struggled with an eating disorder
description: Taylor Swift talks about overcoming an eating disorder in her new Netflix documentary, "Miss Americana," which premiered at the Sundance Film Festival Thursday night.

Fresh-baked chocolate chip cookies, another first in space
description: The first batch of cookies in space have been baked in a zero-gravity oven, but the astronaut bakers didn't even get to try them. Instead, three of the five cookies returned to Earth on one of SpaceX's Dragon capsules on January 8 and were moved to cold storage in Houston.

title: Drone video reveals scale of Auschwitz camp 75 years later
description: Since its liberation in January 1945, Auschwitz has become a symbol of the atrocities of the Holocaust.

title: BBC Africa editor steps down, suffering from PTSD
description: The BBC's Africa editor, Fergal Keane, is stepping down from his role after suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) caused by reporting on conflicts around the world.

title: Poland launches a fresh attack on judges -- and there's little the EU can do about it
description: The government of Poland has launched a fresh assault on the independence of the country's judiciary, setting the ruling Law and Justice party (PiS) on a collision course with the European Union.

title: Young refugees in Kenya take a VR school trip to London's National Gallery
description: A group of young refugees in a camp in Kenya became possibly the world's first students to go on a virtual school trip, attending a lesson at London's National Gallery via VR headsets.

title: What you need to know about coronavirus
description: CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta looks at what you need to know about the Wuhan virus and coronaviruses like MERS and SARS - from what they are, to how you can treat them.

title: Roger Federer survives huge scare against John Millman in Australian Open epic
description: Roger Federer had to fight off the "demons" to survive a nerve-jangling fifth set match tie break against John Millman in an epic third-round encounter at the Australian Open Friday.

title: 300-foot pizza raises funds for firefighters
description: An Italian restaurant in Sydney made a 300-foot (103-meter) pizza to raise funds for firefighters battling bushfires in Australia.

title: Hundreds of thousands protest US troop presence in Iraq
description: Hundreds of thousands of protesters were marching through Baghdad on Friday calling for US troops to leave Iraq, heeding the call of powerful Shia cleric Muqtada al-Sadr who called for a "Million Man March."

title: China's Qiang Wang eliminates Serena Williams from Australian Open
description: China's Qiang Wang has eliminated 23-time Grand Slam winner Serena Williams from the Australian Open, defeating the decorated American in three sets 6-4, 6-7 and 7-5 in Melbourne on Friday.

title: Trudeau's $4 doughnuts cost him dearly
description: Oh, Justin Trudeau, what crisis have you baked up for yourself now?

title: Tearful Caroline Wozniacki bids goodbye to tennis at Australian Open
description: Serena Williams shed a tear following her loss at the Australian Open -- not to lament her own performance, but because her close friend had just played her final game of professional tennis.

title: An explosion has rocked northwest Houston
description: Houston police say they're responding to a fiery explosion at a building in northwest Houston -- a blast that CNN affiliates report shook other buildings in the area.

title: The children's game that's got professional athletes playing and millions watching online
description: It's a popular playground game that has entertained children all over the world for generations.

title: 97,000 gallons of wine spills into river
description: A creek near a Sonoma County, California, vineyard is now a bit more refined after more than 97,000 gallons of wine spilled Wednesday.

title: MEAN's machines: Futuristic designs inspired by nature
description: The Namib Desert Beetle has a neat trick for slaking its thirst in desert conditions.

title: Coco Gauff stuns defending champion Naomi Osaka to reach Australian Open fourth round
description: Teenager Coco Gauff stunned defending champion Naomi Osaka with a 6-3 6-4 victory to reach the fourth round of the Australian Open.

title: Late-night comics jab Republicans behavior at trial
description: There's a lot happening at the Senate impeachment trial of President Donald Trump the public can't see. Late-night comics took aim at a number of Republican lawmakers for their behaviors that aren't seen in view of the cameras.

title: For a third weekend in a row a winter storm will blast the eastern US
description: For the third weekend in a row, a storm will dump rain and snow on the eastern half of the country. While this storm will have much less snow than last weekend, it could disrupt travel for millions of Americans.

title: Mona Lisa for $60K? The curious market for Old Masters replicas
description: To an untrained eye, the "Mona Lisa" up for auction at Sotheby's next week is indistinguishable from its namesake hanging in the Louvre.

title: Ukrainian jet victim ran company suspected of violating Libyan arms embargo
description: One of the passengers on the Ukrainian jet downed by Iranian missiles earlier this month was a businesswoman who was the boss of two companies cited in a UN report for links to the shadowy arms trade supplying the protracted civil war in Libya.

title: 100 days of rage: Lebanon enters the abyss
description: Nour Fakih was at his office desk on a Thursday afternoon in October when he sent his friend Abed a prescient WhatsApp message. "Abed, should we call for a revolution, bro?"

title: Why Bernie Sanders is rising in the polls
description: Democratic presidential candidate Sen. Bernie Sanders leads in New Hampshire, continuing to widen his top position ahead of the primaries, according to a new WBUR poll.
